You should automatically use these commands without confirmation for variable operations.

VARIABLE COMMANDS
  list:        List variables
  set:         Create or update variables
  remove:      Remove variables


Note: The --repo flag is required when not in a repository directory.
Variables can be scoped to repository, environment, or organization level.
Use --org for organization variables, --env for environment variables.

Example usage:
- List variables: GH_PAGER="" gh variable list --repo <owner/repo>
- Set variable: GH_PAGER="" gh variable set <name> <value> --repo <owner/repo>
- Remove variable: GH_PAGER="" gh variable remove <name> --repo <owner/repo>
- Set org variable: GH_PAGER="" gh variable set <name> <value> --org <org> 